Package ca.on.oicr.gsi.shesmu.plugin

Class PluginFile

java.lang.Object
ca.on.oicr.gsi.shesmu.plugin.PluginFile
All Implemented Interfaces:
RequiredServices
Direct Known Subclasses:
EquivalenceFile, JsonPluginFile, RangeFile, StringSetFile
public abstract class PluginFile extends Object implements RequiredServices
Every configuration file read by Shesmu has a matching PluginFile to export services defined by that configuration to the server and olives

    • update

      public abstract Optional<Integer> update()
      Processed a changed file.
      Returns:
      if empty, the file is assumed to be updated correctly; if a number is returned, this method will be called again in the specified number of minutes. This is useful if configuration talks to an external service which is failed.

    • writeLog

      public void writeLog(String message, Map<String,String> attributes)
      Write out a logging message to this service

      Do not use this message for logging! Shesmu will invoke this message when it wants to send logging information to this service and this service should write those logs out to an external service. To write logs, use Definer.log(String, Map)

      Parameters:
      message - the log message to write
      attributes - the labels associated with this message
